#Aircraft Control

>###tl;dr
>In a typical quadcopter, four rotors are mounted in the extremities of the fuselage to provide *Lift* and control.

##Configuration

quad, quad (fore/aft), hex

##Control in the Hover
pitch, roll yaw

##Control in Flight
Note that ‘forward’ is arbitrary and really just a requirement of the camera

climb, descent, translate, yaw (skid)
